article.headline: Wisconsin 70, Green Bay 56
article.story: MADISON, Wis. -- Jon Leuer scored 22 points, Mike Bruesewitz added a career-best 18 and Wisconsin went 10 of 17 from 3-point range to beat Wisconsin-Green Bay 70-56 on Monday night. Wisconsin (9-2) avenged its first ever loss last season to Green Bay (4-7) with a sizzling performance from behind the arc, improving to 16-1 all-time against its in-state neighbor. The Badgers also have wins over Wisconsin-Milwaukee and Marquette, marking the first time since the 2006-07 season that they've swept the other Division I teams in Wisconsin. Keaton Nankivil had 16 points and Jordan Taylor added 10 for Wisconsin, which lost 88-84 in overtime in Green Bay last year. Rahmon Fletcher and freshman Alec Brown each had 18 points for the Phoenix.
